@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}

<main class="container mt-4" aria-labelledby="title">

    <h2 id="title" class="mb-3 text-white bg-dark p-3 rounded shadow">
        About This Application
    </h2>

    <p class="lead">
        This application is a <strong>Student Management System</strong> developed using
        <strong>ASP.NET MVC (Database First Approach)</strong>.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h4 class="mt-4">📌 Project Overview</h4>
    <p>
        The system is designed to efficiently manage student records with a structured and scalable approach.
        It demonstrates core backend development concepts including data handling, business logic implementation,
        and clean architectural design using MVC pattern.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">⚙️ Key Functionalities</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Add, view, update student records</li>
        <li>Upload and manage student profile images</li>
        <li>Soft delete mechanism to preserve data</li>
        <li>Efficient data retrieval using LINQ</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4">🛡️ Data Handling Approach</h4>
    <p>
        Instead of permanently deleting records, the application uses a
        <strong>Soft Delete strategy</strong> where data is marked inactive.
        This ensures data safety, supports recovery, and aligns with real-world enterprise practices.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">🛠️ Technologies Used</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>ASP.NET MVC (C#)</li>
        <li>SQL Server</li>
        <li>LINQ to SQL</li>
        <li>HTML, CSS, Bootstrap</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />

    <p class="text-muted">
        This project reflects practical implementation of backend development concepts and real-world application design.
    </p>

</main>